    computation: "Measure AI: Nsight Compute captures FLOPs via SM metrics and HBM bytes via DRAM throughput. Effective AI = measured_FLOPS / measured_HBM_bytes (higher than theoretical if L2 helps). Target: for FP16 TC on A100, need AI > 156 to be compute-bound.",
    workedExample: "ReLU kernel: for each element: 1 max op = 1 FLOP; 2 bytes read + 2 bytes write = 4 bytes; AI = 1/4 = 0.25 FLOP/byte. At 2 TB/s: 0.25 × 2 TB/s = 500 GFLOPS — tiny. Fuse ReLU into GEMM: same 4 bytes, but also 2MNK FLOP from GEMM → AI ≫ 156 → compute-bound with no added memory traffic.",
